  "folder": "fhSubFantasy0001",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A small purple-capped fungus that grows on rotting logs in marshlands, visually identical to a popular edible variety. Foragers learn to tell the difference; their friends usually don't. Eaten unwittingly more often than not.</p><p><strong><em>Desired effects on use.</em></strong> For 1 hour your sense of color is heightened and faintly synesthetic: you have advantage on Charisma (Performance) checks and disadvantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on sight.</p><p><strong><em>On use, save against addiction.</em></strong> Make a DC 11 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, you gain the Addicted condition from Bogwitch's Prank (see below).</p><p><strong><em>Addicted from Bogwitch's Prank.</em></strong> While you have this Addicted condition, you are also Poisoned and have disadvantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks.</p><p><strong><em>Withdrawal Modifier: 2.</em></strong> Withdrawal lasts max(2 &minus; your Constitution modifier, 1) long rests, minimum 1.</p>"
    },
